{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17500357","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17500357"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T10:12:05+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T10:12:05+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1634"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17582968","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17582968"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:03:07+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:03:07+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1634"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1634","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1634"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.15,0.03,0.03,0.61,0.18]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1634"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"86372"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1634","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1634"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1634"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"70651"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1196"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"5264"},{"type":"tags","id":"9434"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"5373"},{"type":"contributions","id":"6574"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"86372","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/86372"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 60-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic for a routine health check. He currently has no medical concerns. He has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, his teeth show a generalised discolouration (Image). The patient reports these changes have been present since his permanent teeth erupted in childhood.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely explanation for the tooth discolouration?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Excessive consumption of soft drinks","Regular coffee consumption in childhood","Frequent consumption of acidic fruits","Antibiotics in childhood","Excessive fluoride exposure"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe teeth show intrinsic grey-blue discolouration characteristic of \u003Cstrong\u003Etetracycline antibiotics\u003C/strong\u003E exposure during tooth development. When tetracyclines are given while permanent teeth are forming beneath the gums, the drug becomes incorporated into the developing dental tissues. This results in permanent intrinsic staining that becomes visible when the teeth erupt.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExcessive consumption of soft drinks\u003C/strong\u003E can cause dental erosion and extrinsic yellowing of teeth due to their acidic nature, but this does not result in the characteristic grey-blue intrinsic staining pattern seen here.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERegular coffee consumption\u003C/strong\u003E typically causes superficial brown staining of teeth through chromogenic compounds. This extrinsic staining can usually be removed through professional cleaning and does not cause intrinsic grey-blue discolouration.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFrequent consumption of acidic fruits\u003C/strong\u003E may lead to dental erosion and yellowing through enamel wear, but does not cause intrinsic tooth discolouration.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExcessive fluoride exposure\u003C/strong\u003E during tooth development can cause dental fluorosis, characterised by white specks or brown mottling of teeth. It does not cause the uniform grey-blue discolouration seen in tetracycline staining.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe recognition of tetracycline-induced tooth discolouration led to recommendations against using these antibiotics in children under 8 years of age and in pregnant women, as the developing teeth are particularly susceptible to incorporation of the drug.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Tetracycline antibiotics can cause permanent grey-blue discolouration of teeth if given during tooth development.","Dental staining patterns can help differentiate between various causes of tooth discolouration.","Common dietary causes like coffee and soft drinks typically cause superficial yellowing rather than intrinsic tooth staining."],"references":["Vennila V, Madhu V, Rajesh R, Ealla KK, Velidandla SR, Santoshi S. Tetracycline-induced discoloration of deciduous teeth: case series. J Int Oral Health. 2014;6(3):115-9. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25083046/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"70651"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1634"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"16043"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"16043","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/16043"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/78944f98-6770-4eda-8e3d-9a74c3ab204c.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/78944f98-6770-4eda-8e3d-9a74c3ab204c.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":800,"height":600}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"70651","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/70651"},"attributes":{"createdAt"